                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1216: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-18T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 18, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>587. Legation’s 543, July 5, 5 p.m. Following from American Consul at Foochow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 17, 4 p.m. Have arranged to proceed Yenping tomorrow morning with
                            launch to bring down Americans from Lu territory. Both sides have
                            promised safe conduct through fighting lines. No other way possible to
                            effect their evacuation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Commander in Chief informed.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
